{"_id":"gryffindor00000001","name":"Gryffindor","type":"race","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Ability Score Increase: Your Constitution score, Charisma score, and one other ability score of choice increase by 1.</p><p>At first level you gain Inspiring Presence or Bravehearted and True Gryffindor.</p><p>Feat: You gain one feat of your choice.</p>"},"advancement":[{"_id":"gryf-asi-fixed","type":"AbilityScoreImprovement","level":1,"configuration":{"points":0,"fixed":{"con":1,"cha":1},"cap":20}},{"_id":"gryf-asi-choice","type":"AbilityScoreImprovement","level":1,"configuration":{"points":1,"fixed":{},"cap":20}},{"_id":"gryf-choice-1","type":"ItemChoice","level":1,"configuration":{"choices":["gryf-inspiring","gryf-bravehearted"],"type":"feat"},"title":"First Feature"},{"_id":"gryf-grant-true","type":"ItemGrant","level":1,"configuration":{"items":["gryf-true"],"type":"feat"},"title":"True Gryffindor"},{"_id":"gryf-feat","type":"ItemChoice","level":1,"configuration":{"choices":[],"type":"feat","prompt":"Feat: You gain one feat of your choice."},"title":"Feat"}]},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"gryf-inspiring","name":"Inspiring Presence","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Inspiring Presence: When in combat, your friends eagerly stand beside you as a beacon of courage and inspiration. Once per long rest, if an ally within 10 feet of you falls to 0 HP, you may use your reaction to defend them from danger. Using this ability ensures they will regain consciousness at 1 HP. An individual can only benefit from this effect once per day.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"gryf-bravehearted","name":"Bravehearted","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/shield.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Bravehearted: You have advantage on saving throws against being frightened from any source other than a Dementor.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"gryf-true","name":"True Gryffindor","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/sword.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>True Gryffindor: In times of dire need, the Sword of Gryffindor may present itself to you.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hufflepuff0000001","name":"Hufflepuff","type":"race","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Ability Score Increase: Your Constitution score, Wisdom score, and one other ability score of choice increase by 1.</p><p>At first level you gain Words of Encouragement or Neg D4, and either Steadfast Loyalty or Kitchen Trips.</p><p>Feat: You gain one feat of your choice.</p>"},"advancement":[{"_id":"huff-asi-fixed","type":"AbilityScoreImprovement","level":1,"configuration":{"points":0,"fixed":{"con":1,"wis":1},"cap":20}},{"_id":"huff-asi-choice","type":"AbilityScoreImprovement","level":1,"configuration":{"points":1,"fixed":{},"cap":20}},{"_id":"huff-choice-1","type":"ItemChoice","level":1,"configuration":{"choices":["huff-words","huff-neg"],"type":"feat"},"title":"First Feature"},{"_id":"huff-choice-2","type":"ItemChoice","level":1,"configuration":{"choices":["huff-steadfast","huff-kitchen"],"type":"feat"},"title":"Second Feature"},{"_id":"huff-feat","type":"ItemChoice","level":1,"configuration":{"choices":[],"type":"feat","prompt":"Feat: You gain one feat of your choice."},"title":"Feat"}]},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"huff-words","name":"Words of Encouragement","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/chat.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Words of Encouragement: You may use your reaction to give an ally who can hear you, a d4 bonus to the first attack roll, ability check, or saving throw they make before the start of your next turn. You may use this ability a number of times per long rest equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of 1). A target may only benefit from this effect once per round.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"huff-neg","name":"Neg D4","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/chemical-bolt.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Neg D4: You may use your reaction to give a creature who can hear you, a d4 penalty to any attack roll, ability check, or saving throw they make before the start of your next turn. You may use this ability a number of times per long rest equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of 1). A target may only be penalized from this effect once per round.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"huff-steadfast","name":"Steadfast Loyalty","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/angel.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Steadfast Loyalty: You have advantage on saving throws against any effect that would make you attack or work against a creature you would normally consider an ally.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"huff-kitchen","name":"Kitchen Trips","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/beer.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Kitchen Trips: Your experience with the Hogwarts house elves has taught you how to politely address and interact with magical beings. Oh, and you can get tons of snacks.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ravenclaw0000001","name":"Ravenclaw","type":"race","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Ability Score Increase: Your Intelligence score, Wisdom score, and one other ability score of choice increase by 1.</p><p>In-Depth Knowledge: Whenever you make an Intelligence or Wisdom ability check that lets you add your proficiency bonus, you can treat a d20 roll of 5 or lower as a 6.</p><p>Rowena's Library: You can easily research a desired topic through enlisting your housemates' help and browsing books exclusively found in the Ravenclaw common room.</p><p>Feat: You gain one feat of your choice.</p>"},"advancement":[{"_id":"rav-asi-fixed","type":"AbilityScoreImprovement","level":1,"configuration":{"points":0,"fixed":{"int":1,"wis":1},"cap":20}},{"_id":"rav-asi-choice","type":"AbilityScoreImprovement","level":1,"configuration":{"points":1,"fixed":{},"cap":20}},{"_id":"rav-grant-1","type":"ItemGrant","level":1,"configuration":{"items":["rav-depth","rav-library"],"type":"feat"},"title":"House Features"},{"_id":"rav-feat","type":"ItemChoice","level":1,"configuration":{"choices":[],"type":"feat","prompt":"Feat: You gain one feat of your choice."},"title":"Feat"}]},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"rav-depth","name":"In-Depth Knowledge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/eye.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>In-Depth Knowledge: Whenever you make an Intelligence or Wisdom ability check that lets you add your proficiency bonus, you can treat a d20 roll of 5 or lower as a 6.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"rav-library","name":"Rowena's Library","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Rowena's Library: You can easily research a desired topic through enlisting your housemates' help and browsing books exclusively found in the Ravenclaw common room.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"slytherin0000001","name":"Slytherin","type":"race","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Ability Score Increase: Your Dexterity score, Charisma score, and one other ability score of choice increase by 1.</p><p>Compromising Information: Whenever you make a Charisma check related to using a person's secrets, you are considered proficient in the appropriate skill and add double your proficiency bonus to the check, instead of your normal proficiency bonus.</p><p>A Noble Quality: You're able to adopt a persona of importance to blend in among high-ranking officials and prestigious witches and wizards.</p><p>Feat: You gain one feat of your choice.</p>"},"advancement":[{"_id":"sly-asi-fixed","type":"AbilityScoreImprovement","level":1,"configuration":{"points":0,"fixed":{"dex":1,"cha":1},"cap":20}},{"_id":"sly-asi-choice","type":"AbilityScoreImprovement","level":1,"configuration":{"points":1,"fixed":{},"cap":20}},{"_id":"sly-grant-1","type":"ItemGrant","level":1,"configuration":{"items":["sly-compromise","sly-noble"],"type":"feat"},"title":"House Features"},{"_id":"sly-feat","type":"ItemChoice","level":1,"configuration":{"choices":[],"type":"feat","prompt":"Feat: You gain one feat of your choice."},"title":"Feat"}]},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"sly-compromise","name":"Compromising Information","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Compromising Information: Whenever you make a Charisma check related to using a person's secrets, you are considered proficient in the appropriate skill and add double your proficiency bonus to the check, instead of your normal proficiency bonus.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
{"_id":"sly-noble","name":"A Noble Quality","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/crown.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>A Noble Quality: You're able to adopt a persona of importance to blend in among high-ranking officials and prestigious witches and wizards.</p>"}},"effects":[],"flags":{}}
